section.para:
A service handler binding type is a Java annotation defined as
        @Target({TYPE, METHOD}) or @Target(TYPE) and
        @Retention(RUNTIME).

The service handler binding of a service handler is specified by annotating the service
      handler class with the binding type and the
        @javax.servicehandler.ServiceHandler annotation.

section.programlisting:
@QueryService @ServiceHandler
public class QueryServiceHandler {

   @Inject    
   javax.persistence.EntityManager em;     

   @AroundInvoke 
   public Object handleQueryInvocation(InvocationContext ctx) throws Exception {
      return em.createQuery(ctx.getMethod().getAnnotation(Query.class).value()).getResultList();
   }

}

@QueryService
public interface ProductDAO{

     @Query("select obj from Product obj where obj.productName like ?")
     List<Product> getAllProducts();

}
